<div class="sidebarRightData">
	<div class="img"><img src="css/img/KbinaryCircle.png"></div>
	<h2>Konstruct - Open Source Fest</h2>
	<h3>Open Source at WBUT</h3>
	<p>Open source as a development model promotes a universal access via a free license to a product's design or blueprint, and universal redistribution of that design or blueprint, including subsequent improvements to it by anyone. Opening the source code enabled a self-enhancing diversity of production models, communication paths, and interactive communities.<br>
At Konstruct 2015 we the students of WBUT have endeavored to capture this spirit by bringing together stalwarts in the field of OSS like Mozilla, Linux Users Group, and Java Users Group. <br>
We also are proud to announce that this event will mark a new chapter of DEFCON India (or NULL) based out of Kolkata! <br>
Internshala will be present to share their pearls of wisdom with us, and last but definitely not the least we have Jimmy Tangree for India Records hosting a seminar for us on the second day.<br>
As Kolkata's first Open Source Fest kicks off the great words of Linus Torvalds once again comes to mind:<br><b><i>&quotTalk is cheap. Show me the code.&quot</i></b><br>Enjoy!</p>
